	<h1 class="title-header">Meet the Team of Center for Retail Transformation</h1>
	<div class="entry-content clearfix">


<br>	
<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="alignleft size-large"><%=image_tag("gautham_white.jpg", size: "220")%><figcaption>        </figcaption></figure></div>



<p><strong>Vadakkepatt, G <br>Assistant Professor, School of Business </strong></p>



<p>Gautham Vadakkepatt is Assistant Professor in Marketing and the director of the Center for Retail Transformation at the School of Business, George Mason University <br></p>



<p>Dr.Vadakkepatt’s research examines the impact of a firm’s technology, social media and non-product strategies (e.g., lobbying, CSR, social activism) on customer experience and firm performance. His research has been published in theJournal of Marketing, Journal of Retailing, Journal of Interactive Marketing, Journal of Business Research, Journal of Public Policy and Marketing,andMarketing Science Institute Reports.He is the recipient of the discipline-wide2015 MSI/H. Paul Root Awardfrom theJournal of Marketing and Marketing Science Institute and thefinalist for the 2020 Sheth Foundation/Journal of Marketing Award for long-term contributions to the field of marketing. Gautham serves on the editorial review board of the Journal of Business Research (Retail) and the Journal of Public Policy and Marketing, and serve as an ad-hoc reviewer for the Journal of Marketing, Academy of Marketing Science Review, Journal of Interactive Marketing, and Journal of Retailing. In addition, In addition he as co-editor for a special issue on political activity and marketing for the Journal of Public Policy and Marketing.Prior to joining academia, Dr. Vadakkepatt worked for General Electric. He has also consulted with several start-ups and public corporations on various elements of marketing strategy</p>

<br>

<hr>

	
<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="alignleft size-large"><%=image_tag("rushabh.jpg", size: "220")%><figcaption>        </figcaption></figure></div>



<p><strong>Ostawal, R <br>Graduate Research Assistant </strong></p>



<p>Rishabh Ostawal is pursuing his Masters degree in Computer Science and is also a Graduate Research Assistant at the School of Business, George Mason University.<br></p>



<p>For Center of Retail Transformation, Rishabh works on Data Scraping for the analysis and also as a Software Developer. Rishabh's expertise is in Systems Programming, Application/Web Development and also Cyber Security. Prior to joining George Mason for his Masters course, he completed his Bachelors in Computer Science and Engineering.</p>

<br>

<hr>


<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="alignleft size-large"><%=image_tag("srikaran.jpeg", size: "220")%></figure></div>



<p><strong>Elakurthy, S <br>Graduate Research Assistant </strong></p>

<p>Srikaran Elakurthy is pursuing his Masters in Data Analytics and also a Graduate Research Assistant at the school of Business, George Mason University.<br></p>

<p>For Center of Retail Transformation, Srikaran works on the Social media analysis and built sentiment and topic model ping analysis models to find the patterns and relate it to stock trends concentrated on text mining. Srikaran’s expertise lies in NLP with Machine learning , deep learning and Data mining. Prior to Masters he has an experience of 2 years as a software developer and as a research scientist on wealth management of Fintech and completed his Bachelor’s in Computer Science.</p>

